OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FByron statue move planned  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25F66 years after go-ahead    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A descendent of Lord Byron wants a     
OL,6, statue of the poet moved from a traffic
OL,7, island in central London.              
OL,9,FThe Earl of Lytton cited a government  
OL,10,Fpledge made in 1958 during a debate on 
OL,11,Fthe then new Park Lane traffic scheme. 
OL,13,FLord Lytton, Byron's                   
OL,14,Fgreat-great-great-grandson, said the   
OL,15,Fbronze, created in 1880 by sculptor    
OL,16,FRichard Belt, "languishes" in an       
OL,17,Fisolated spot.                         
OL,19,FOn the bicentenary of the poet's death,
OL,20,Fthe Byron Society is fundraising to get
OL,21,Fit moved to Hyde Park.                 
